    "body": "Thank you for raising this @dnkolegov :pray: It is indeed an issue and I have a fix over at #2517. We will include this in our next release.\r\n\r\nIn my testing I noticed that it's only `POST` requests that are missing header checks, whilst both `GET` and `PATCH` are checked. This is at odds with your description; you stated that `PATCH` was also passing without header checks.\r\n\r\nThe only reason I'm raising this is to make sure that I didn't miss something with the `PATCH` requests.\r\n\r\n### Examples\r\n\r\nPATCH indicates a missing header:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X PATCH localhost:5062/lighthouse/validators\r\n{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"BAD_REQUEST: missing Authorization header\",\"stacktraces\":[]}\r\n```\r\n\r\nPOST indicates an invalid body (meaning it didn't check the headers):\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST localhost:5062/lighthouse/validators\r\n{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"BAD_REQUEST: body deserialize error: Request body deserialize error: EOF while parsing a value at line 1 column 0\",\"stacktraces\":[]}\r\n```",
